The following are prices paid for
cocoa at the main growing centers in  Ivory Coast  from March 26
to March 31, according to the figures published by the Bourse du
Cafe et du Cacao on its website.  The national average paid was 681  CFA francs  ($1.36) per
kilogram (2.2 pounds), the state-run bourse said. The highest
price was 700 francs and the lowest 650 francs. The West African
nation is the worldâ€™s biggest cocoa producer.  Ivory Coast set the indicative farmgate cocoa price for the
2011-2012 season at 1,000 CFA francs on Oct. 3. Prices are in
CFA francs per kilogram ($1 = 499 CFA francs).  To contact the reporter on this story:
